## Investigation Steps

1. Identify the modified group.
2. Determine which account was added.
3. Verify who performed the action.
4. Confirm whether the change was authorized.
5. Review related authentication events.

---

## Conclusion

Unexpected administrator group changes may indicate privilege escalation or unauthorized administrative access.
